sql:
SELECT wins, losses
FROM last_10
WHERE team_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- The performance score is calculated as a weighted average of the team's overall win percentage (70%) and their win percentage in the last 10 games (30%), minus their average pitching ERA.;
- A higher performance score indicates better overall performance.;
- The win percentage and recent form are positive factors, while a lower ERA (indicating better pitching) is also a positive factor.;
- The teams are ranked from highest to lowest performance score.

- A strong recent performance is indicated by a team's win percentage of at least 0.6 and more wins than losses in the last 10 games;
- Notable history of batting is defined by having more than three recorded batting average statistics;
- The batting average is a measure of a player's performance in baseball, calculated by the number of hits divided by the number of at-bats.

- ERA (Earned Run Average) is a statistic in baseball that measures the average number of earned runs a pitcher allows per nine innings pitched;
- The "last 10 games" refers to the most recent 10 games played by each team;
- "Star pitchers" are the pitchers who are consistently performing and contributing to the team's performance.

- 'Shining star' refers to the team performing the best;
- 'Leading the pack' means the team is ranked highest;
- 'Best performance this month' includes the team's recent wins, losses, and overall standing.

sql:
